==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scrupulosity
<hw>Scru`pu*los"i*ty</hw>
<pr>(skr⟦udd⟧`p⟦usl⟧*l⟦ocr⟧s"⟦icr⟧*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>scrupulositas</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
scrupulous; doubt; doubtfulness respecting decision or action; caution
or tenderness from the fear of doing wrong or offending; nice regard to
exactness and propriety; precision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The first sacrilege is looked on with horror; but when they have
made the breach, their <qex>scrupulosity</qex> soon retires.</q>
<rj><qau>Dr. H. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Careful, even to <qex>scrupulosity</qex>, . . . to keep their
Sabbath.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scrupulous</ent>⟦br⟧
